headline: Charles Schwab (SCHW): Reassessing Valuation After Jobs Report Sparks Market Pullback
summary: If you’re watching Charles Schwab (SCHW) this week, you probably noticed the stock’s dip after the latest jobs report rattled investors. The U.S. economy added just 22,000 jobs for August, a figure that landed well below forecasts and quickly shifted the mood for markets. With fears of a downturn surfacing, banking and financial stocks, including Schwab, took a hit as concerns about the broader economic outlook nudged risk appetites lower. This move comes at a surprisingly strong stretch for...
